.IP \(bu 2n
the RCS history commands in the aegis user guide all use the `-u'
option for `ci' to check out a copy after registering/updating
a file.  However `ci -u' always does keyword expansion.  To avoid
this, we have omitted the -u, so the working file is gone after
the `ci'.  We check it out again using `co', this time with the
`-ko' option to avoid keyword expansion.
.\"
.\"	history_create_command =
.\"		"ci -f -d -M -m$c -t/dev/null '$i' '$h,v'; rcs -U '$h,v';\
.\"             co -ko -u '$i' '$h,v'";
.\"	history_put_command =
.\"		"ci -f -d -M -m$c '$i' '$h,v'; co -ko -u '$i' '$h,v'";
.\"	history_get_command =
.\"		"co -ko -r'$e' -p '$h,v' > '$o'";
.\"
Note that the -ko option is always given to the `co' command,
never to `ci' or `rcs'.
Submitted: Ralf Fassel <ralf@akutech.de>, 18 Jan 2000
